  <bioghist id="aspace_418d3fd848bc69bad883e4d2238bd6f4">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>David Smith was a union organizer in Cleveland, Ohio for the Cleveland Industrial Union Council in 1941. He began naval training as an Aviation Machinist at the Ford Navy Service School in Dearborn Michigan in 1942, but was held by Naval Intelligence after graduation due to suspected subversive activity before advancing to full naval service from 1942 to 1945. In 1945 David Smith married Esther Frank after writing to her extensively during his three years of naval service. </p><p>Esther Smith (nee Frank), of the Bronx, New York served as Executive Secretary to the Town and Village Tenants' Committee to End Discrimination in Stuyvesant Town, and fought against the attempted eviction of anti-discrimination activists from Stuyvesant Town by the corporate landlord, Metropolitan Life Insurance Agency.</p>  </bioghist>
